#week-title("Three", "Desoille's Intense Light: The Rubedo")

=== Core Teaching

The final stage of Robert Desoille's ascending movement is the disappearance of
symbolic imagery, replaced by a perception of *Intense Light*. He associates
this with Cosmic Consciousness — the threshold where the personal ego approaches
union with the universal Source.

This corresponds to the Rubedo in its fullest psychological expression. While the
Year One student will not have reached this in its fullness, the *Rubedo waking
dream practice* establishes a personal baseline for the three years of inner
work ahead.

=== Topics This Week

- Characteristics of the Rubedo zone
- Moving beyond archetypal imagery to pure perception
- Baseline setting for Year Two

#inner-work[
  *The Rubedo Waking Dream*

  Sit in meditation. Ascend through the previous stages (Descending → Dawn →
  Day). Go as far as the imagery will naturally take you.

  Do not force the intense light — simply ascend until the imagery stops. Whatever
  the highest state reached, record it honestly. This is your baseline. Record
  the sensory qualities of the highest state reached.
]

